# Small-file read benchmark — exercises readdir + open + read + close
# for many tiny files, rather than streaming a single large file.
# This stresses the metadata path more than the data path.
#
# NOTE: This suite uses a shell-based benchmark instead of fio because
# fio has compatibility issues with FUSE mounts (ENOSYS on open, file
# size detection).  The runner script handles it specially via
# run_small_files_suite().

# This file is intentionally left as documentation only.
# The actual benchmark is run by scripts/bench-read.sh.